&nbsp;Durban - Five new vehicles valued at R2 million were stolen from a dealership, Mascor Toyota Greytown Sunday night.The vehicles included Hilux bakkies, a Fortuner and a Land Cruiser.Police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said a security guard was held up Sunday night by a group of armed men at the dealership in Dr Wessels Avenue.Zwane said they tied the guard up, took his cellphone and instructed him to be silent.Police were not sure how the men got the cars out.A case of business robbery has been opened at Greytown police station for investigation.Daily News Reporter